Author-Name: CAMPBELL, GERARD M.
Abstract: In a multiproduct, parallel machine environment, it may be beneficial to dedicate one or more of the machines to a single product for consecutive time periods. However, previous lot-sizing and scheduling models usually do not allow for such short-term dedication. This paper presents a mixed-integer programming model that allows for short-term dedication in scheduling parallel machines serving multiple products with dynamic demands. It also describes a Lagrangian-based algorithm for solving such scheduling problems.
